<h1>Home Repairs</h1>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Do any twelve (12) of the following:
<ol type=a>
<li>Know the location of your main electric switch. Replace a fuse or rest the circuit breaker in the electric entrance switch box.
<li>Repair a sagging or squeaking door or gate.
<li>Repair a break in a cement walk or wall.
<li>Recondition a garden tool.
<li>Repair broken furniture.
<li>Refinish or repair the scratched surface of a piece of furniture. Clean brush afterwards.
<li>Repair or replace broken window shells (at least five), or replace a window pane or jalousie.
<li>Repair a leaking roof.
<li>Repair a leaking faucet.
<li>Repair a leaky hose.
<li>Mend a broken bolo handle.
<li>Repair a pressure gas lamp or stove.
<li>Recane the broken seat of a chair or bed frame.
<li>Clean out a clogged sink trap.
<li>Mend a torn mat.
<li>Repair the flushing mechanism in the water closet.
<li>Repair an electric cord, plug, or electric socket.
<li>Paint a wall or ceiling. Clean brush afterwards.
<li>Repair a flat iron.
<li>Repair a gas stove.
<li>Mend broken china.
<li>Build a workbench.
<li>Repair or put in drapery or curtain rods. Hang draperies or curtains.
<li>Repair a fence.
<li>Replace a door knob.
<li>Solder.</ol><p>

<li>Name and describe some common tools used for doing home repairs.</ol>



</span><p>    </td>
